2. Key findings per component
Softeria ms-365-mcp-server (Node.js, not Python)
This is a mature, 661-star MCP server that covers 200+ Graph API tools across Mail, Calendar, OneDrive, Teams, Contacts, ToDo, Planner, OneNote, and Search. It supports stdio and HTTP transports, OAuth2 with MSAL, multi-account mode, and tool presets (mail, calendar, files, etc.) to limit context load. Critical note: it is written in Node.js, not Python. This is relevant ΓÇö your FastMCP Python tools will run alongside it, not replace it. A known production risk exists: the OAuth token-sharing approach in HTTP mode has a race-condition bug reported by a contributor in the BYOT discussion. For a multi-user enterprise deployment this needs careful handling.
ForLegalAI mcp-ms-office-documents (Python + Docker)
This generates Office files (pptx, docx, eml, xlsx) on demand. It runs as a Docker service on port 8958 with StreamableHTTP transport, and has native LibreChat integration instructions including shared Docker network config. It supports reusable templates (YAML-defined email templates, docx with {{placeholders}}). Excellent fit for MOM drafts, email drafts, and summary documents.
LibreChat MCP integration
LibreChat registers MCP servers in librechat.yaml under mcpServers. Both stdio and streamable HTTP transports are supported. The BYOT discussion confirms OAuth token pass-through is the correct pattern: LibreChat holds the userΓÇÖs OAuth token and injects it as a header or env var into the MCP server call. The key config line is MS365_MCP_OAUTH_TOKEN={{TOKEN}}. LibreChat also supports Agent Builder with granular per-tool toggling, Deferred Tools (lazy-load to save context), and Programmatic Tool Calling for multi-step workflows. MCP servers must be restarted to pick up config changes.
FastMCP (Python)
FastMCP 3.x is the de facto standard Python MCP framework ΓÇö 1M downloads/day, powers 70% of MCP servers across all languages. Decorator-based (@mcp.tool), full async/sync support, OAuth 2.1, Keycloak/Azure support, middleware (auth, logging, rate limiting), persistent state, and streamable HTTP. This is your primary build framework for custom Python MCP tools.
Requesty.AI
An LLM gateway (400+ models, OpenAI-compatible API) that replaces direct provider calls. Since the blueprint forbids Claude and OpenAI models, Requesty lets you route to Gemini, Mistral, DeepSeek, Meta Llama, or any other provider via one endpoint. It adds fallback chains, semantic caching, cost controls, and governance. One line of code: base_url="https://router.requesty.ai/v1". It also has a native MCP Gateway feature.
Microsoft Graph SDK for Python
msgraph-sdk-python is the official Microsoft Python SDK. Handles delegated auth (user-on-behalf-of), app-only auth, and supports all the Graph endpoints you need. This is what your FastMCP tools will call internally.
MongoDB
Used by LibreChat natively for conversation storage. Your platform will extend this to also store email metadata/index, extracted tasks, MOM records, and follow-up reminders.

